Section : Preparation (20) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
1. Ensure image and BIOS are appropriate.
2. Make sure DUT passes Microphone Airtightness test.
3. Test environment:A quiet room/office that ambient noise<35dBA.
4. Test requirement:1*Sound Level Meter;4*BGN speaker,1*Speech speaker(MRP).
5. Refer to picture 'Test Room Setup' and place DUT & speakers: DUT position is in the center of the table,while maintaining same distance from each BGN speaker. Speech Speaker position is 80cm away in front of DUT.
6. Please download the latest case tool.
7. Record Tool:Cool Edit. Record with Mono Channel. Cool Edit->Analyze->Statistics->Total RMS Power.
8. If support â€œAIæ™ºèƒ½åœºæ™¯/Smart sceneâ€, Microphone effects will be disabled automatically when recording with music playback, please turn off this function.
9. Pure voice UI has been removed, please download Smart Noise Cancellation app for performance test in Microsoft store.
For Fortemedia & AIspeech, please search fortemedia or Aispeech in Microsoft store. For Elevoc, please download from https://apps.microsoft.com/detail/9P9N9H8TFH9P.
10. Please remember to record first for all test and fill the test result in the report.
 
Section : Beam Forming (25) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Refer to picture 'Beam Forming' and place DUT & Speech speaker
Private Mode
1. Calibrate Speech speaker 65dBA @DUT by 'Speech_LevelCalibration.wav'.
2. Select Private Mode.
3. Refer to picture '360 scale' and move DUT to a different angle, please cover degree(150deg, 180deg, 210deg) & in-beam degree (0deg, 30deg, 330deg) & out-beam degree (60deg, 270deg, 300deg).
4. Start recording the audio file on the DUT and payback 'Speech.wav' file on Speech Speaker.
Notes: If project is 3D Microphone Topology, (150deg, 180deg, 210deg) signal will be supressed, difference value>20 +-2dB, please fill result in the excel sheet 'Beam Forming2' (3D Mic Topology).
5. Play the recorded file.
Ensure (150deg, 180deg, 210deg) & in-beam degree speech recording no sound glitch and discontinue.
6. Record the Total RMS Power of out-beam degree recorded file and fill in report.
Ensure each out-beam signal be supressed, check the out-beam difference value>20 +-2dB.
7. Refer to picture 'Beam Forming' and place in-beam speaker(0deg)&out-beam speaker(45deg/90deg).
Calibrate in-beam&out-beam Speech speaker 65dBA @DUT by 'Speech_LevelCalibration.wav'.
8. Start recording the audio file on the DUT and playback 'Speech.wav' file on in-beam speaker.
9. Record the Total RMS Power and name it in-beam_0deg.
10. Play the recorded file.
Ensure no sound glitch and discontinue.
11. Record the audio file on the DUT and playback 'Speech for outbeam.wav' file on out-beam(45deg) Speaker.
12. Record the Total RMS Power and name it out-beam_45deg. Compare the recording RMS Power of in-beam_0deg&out-beam_45deg.
|out-beam_45deg - in-beam_0deg|>20dBA.
13. Record the audio file on the DUT and playback 'Speech for outbeam.wav' file on out-beam(90deg) Speaker.
14. Record the Total RMS Power to outbeam_90deg. Compare the recording RMS Power of in-beam_0deg&out-beam_90deg.
|out-beam_90deg - in-beam_0deg|>20dBA.
15. Start recording the audio file on the DUT and playback 'Speech.wav' file on in-beam speaker(0deg) & playback 'Speech for outbeam.wav' file on out-beam Speaker(45deg or 90deg) simultaneously.
16. Play the recorded file.
Ensure no sound glitch and discontinue, in beam speech clear as expected.

Section : Echo Cancellation (20) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Calibrate Speech speaker 65dBA @DUT by 'Speech_LevelCalibration.wav'.
Echo Calibration:Playback 'EchoCalibration.wav' on DUT and ensure echo level 65dBA @ DUT.
Private Mode
1. Select Private mode.
2. Start recording the audio file on the DUT and playback 'EchoCalibration' file on the DUT.
3. Record the Total RMS Power of recorded file and name it AEC1_on.
4. Select Off Mode.
5. Repeat step2 and record the Total RMS Power of recorded file and name it AEC1_off.
6. Compare the Total RMS Power of AEC1_on&AEC1_off.
Echo Cancellation Performance Criteria:|AEC1_on - AEC1_off|>25dBA.
7. Select Private mode.
8. Start recording the audio file on the DUT and playback 'Speech.wav' file on Speech Speaker.
9. Record the Total RMS Power of recorded file and name it DTL1.
10. Start recording the audio file on the DUT.
11. Playback 'Speech.wav' file on Speech Speaker and playback 'Echo-EDU.wav' file on DUT simultaneously.
12. Play the recorded file.
Ensure no sound glitch and discontinue with speech recording.
13. Record the Total RMS Power of recorded file and name it DTL2.
14. Compare the Total RMS Power of DTL1&DTL2.
Double talk loss Criteria:|DTL1 - DTL2|<3dBA.
Shared Mode
15. Select Shared mode.
16. Repeat step2-6,record and compare the Total RMS Power of AEC2_on&AEC2_off.
Echo Cancellation Performance Criteria:|AEC2_on - AEC2_off|>25dBA.
17. Select Shared mode.
18. Repeat step8-14,record and compare the Total RMS Power of DTL3&DTL4.
Double talk loss Criteria:|DTL3 - DTL4|<3dBA.
19. Play the recorded file.
Ensure noise will be suppressed; Speech clear as expected
 
Section : Spacial Mode Check (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Notes: Only this test record with Stereo Channel
Refer to picture 'Spacial Mode' and place DUT & 2 Speech Speaker.
Spacial Mode
1. Calibrate 2 Speech Speaker 65dBA @ DUT by 'Speech_LevelCalibration.wav'.
2. Move your mouse to â€œShare modeâ€ button, click the button â€œSpacial modeâ€ upon button â€œShare modeâ€
3. Start recording the audio file on the DUT. Play 'Target test.wav' on 90deg Speech Speaker.
4. When the speaker finishes playing, Play 'Target test.wav' on 270deg Speech Speaker.
5. Record and play the audio file.

Section : Howling Check (15) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Private Mode
1.Prepare two units that have passed microphone airtightnesss test.
Refer to 'howling environment' and place two units.
2. Move two unit make the distance of A&B keep 40 cm.
3. Playback 'howling suppression test audio' on Unit A.
4. Change the MIC&Speaker volume to maximum on two units
5. Reduce Unit A's Speaker Volume if Speech Level > 83 dBA .
6. Ensure Speech Level <= 83 dBA @ Unit B Microphone.
7. Repeat step 3-6 do the same setting on Unit B.
8.Install and login WeChat app on two units
If installed WeChat app is 4.0.0 or newest version, please turn on (AI æ™ºèƒ½åœºæ™¯/Smart scene) in PCM/Vantage, make sure under Meeting mode
PCM: AIæ™ºèƒ½åœºæ™¯->è‡ªåŠ¨æŽ¢æµ‹åœºæ™¯ Vantage: Modes->automatic
9.Select off mode on two units and establish a voice call between two units
ensure howling noise is not be suppressed during voice call
10.Select private mode on two unitsï¼Œestablish a voice call between two units
No howling noise exist during voice callï¼Œa little howling noise can be accepted
11.Please download right vender howling test tool(eg.Elevoc/AIspeech/Fortemedia), follow SOP check the tool result.
The result is pass
 
Section : Meeting Scenes Noise Suppression (55) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Downlink Noise Suppression
1. Turn off all other Audio Render third party effects (e.g. Dolby/Harman/Nahimic/NVIDIA Broadcast).
2. Adjust Internal Speaker output level to default setting (generally 67%)
3. Please download right vender Downlink Noise Suppression test tool(eg.Elevoc/AIspeech/Fortemedia), follow SOP check tool result
The result is pass
Tencent Meeting and DingTalk app(Please cover internal speaker & headphone)
1. Prepare two project unit Tester PC and DUT that have passed Microphone Airtightness test.
2. Connect to a stable networkï¼Œdownload and install Tencent Meeting app on two units.
3. Turn off all other Audio Render third party effects (e.g. Dolby/Harman/Nahimic) on DUT
4. Adjust Internal Speaker output level to default setting (generally 67%) on two units.
5. Open sound control panel/recordingï¼Œenable and set 'stereo mix' as default on Tester PC.
6. Turn off 'Speaker(Downlink) Noise Suppression' with Smart Noise Cancellation app on DUT.
7. Turn off 'Audio noise cancellation' in app settingsï¼Œstart a meeting with two units.
8. Playback 'Whisper3downlinkTest.wav' on Tester PC.
9. Listen carefully on the DUT
Noise will not be suppressed.
10. Turn on 'Speaker(Downlink) Noise Suppression' with Smart Noise Cancellation app on DUTï¼Œrepeat step 8-9.
Ensure noise will be suppressed; Speech clear as expected
11. Download and install DingTalk app on two unitsï¼Œrepeat step 3-10.
Ensure noise will be suppressed; Speech clear as expected
Uplink(Microphone) Noise Suppression
1. Make sure Meeting enhancement(if support) is off in Smart Noise Cancellation app.
Meeting enhancement supports uplink noise reduction in VoIP raw mode app such as Teams.
2. Prepare two project unit Tester PC and DUT that have passed Microphone Airtightness test.
3. Connect to a stable network, download and install Microsoft Teams app on two units.
4. Turn off Noise suppression and Automatic microphone adjustment in Microsoft Teams app device settings.
5. Start a meeting with two units by Microsoft Teams.
Noise will not be suppressed.
6. Make sure Meeting enhancement is on in Smart Noise Cancellation app.
7. Start a meeting with two units by Microsoft Teams.
Noise will be suppressed; Speech clear as expected.
